<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Patch Notes - v8.0.6</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/stylesheets/style.css">
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Orbitron:wght@400;700;900&family=Inter:wght@300;400;600;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
  <style>
    body {
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0f172a 0%, #1e293b 100%);
      color: #e2e8f0;
      font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
      min-height: 100vh;
    }
    .notes-container {
      max-width: 1000px;
      margin: 2rem auto;
      padding: 2rem;
      background: rgba(30, 41, 59, 0.8);
      border-radius: 12px;
      box-shadow: 0 8px 32px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
      border: 1px solid rgba(148, 163, 184, 0.2);
    }
    .notes-header {
      text-align: center;
      padding-bottom: 2rem;
      border-bottom: 2px solid rgba(99, 102, 241, 0.5);
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
    }
    .notes-header h1 {
      font-family: 'Orbitron', sans-serif;
      font-size: 2.5rem;
      margin: 0;
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #6366f1 0%, #8b5cf6 100%);
      -webkit-background-clip: text;
      -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
      background-clip: text;
    }
    .notes-meta {
      display: flex;
      justify-content: center;
      gap: 2rem;
      margin-top: 1rem;
      font-size: 0.875rem;
      color: #94a3b8;
    }
    .section {
      margin-bottom: 3rem;
    }
    .section h2 {
      font-family: 'Orbitron', sans-serif;
      color: #6366f1;
      margin-top: 0;
      margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
      font-size: 1.75rem;
      padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
      border-bottom: 2px solid rgba(99, 102, 241, 0.3);
    }
    .section h3 {
      color: #8b5cf6;
      margin-top: 1.5rem;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
      font-size: 1.25rem;
    }
    .section h4 {
      color: #a78bfa;
      margin-top: 1rem;
      margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
      font-size: 1.1rem;
    }
    .section p {
      line-height: 1.8;
      color: #cbd5e1;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }
    .section ul {
      list-style: none;
      padding-left: 0;
    }
    .section ul li {
      padding-left: 1.5rem;
      margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
      position: relative;
      line-height: 1.6;
    }
    .section ul li:before {
      content: "▸";
      position: absolute;
      left: 0;
      color: #6366f1;
      font-weight: bold;
    }
    .badge {
      display: inline-block;
      padding: 0.25rem 0.75rem;
      border-radius: 4px;
      font-size: 0.75rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      margin-left: 0.5rem;
      text-transform: uppercase;
    }
    .badge-new {
      background: rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.2);
      color: #4ade80;
      border: 1px solid #4ade80;
    }
    .badge-fix {
      background: rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.2);
      color: #60a5fa;
      border: 1px solid #60a5fa;
    }
    .badge-breaking {
      background: rgba(239, 68, 68, 0.2);
      color: #f87171;
      border: 1px solid #f87171;
    }
    .badge-improvement {
      background: rgba(168, 85, 247, 0.2);
      color: #c084fc;
      border: 1px solid #c084fc;
    }
    .warning-box {
      background: rgba(239, 68, 68, 0.1);
      border-left: 4px solid #ef4444;
      padding: 1rem 1.5rem;
      margin: 1.5rem 0;
      border-radius: 4px;
    }
    .warning-box strong {
      color: #f87171;
    }
    .info-box {
      background: rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.1);
      border-left: 4px solid #3b82f6;
      padding: 1rem 1.5rem;
      margin: 1.5rem 0;
      border-radius: 4px;
    }
    .info-box strong {
      color: #60a5fa;
    }
    .back-button {
      display: inline-block;
      margin: 2rem auto;
      padding: 0.75rem 2rem;
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #6366f1 0%, #8b5cf6 100%);
      color: white;
      text-decoration: none;
      border-radius: 6px;
      font-weight: 600;
      transition: transform 0.2s, box-shadow 0.2s;
      text-align: center;
    }
    .back-button:hover {
      transform: translateY(-2px);
      box-shadow: 0 8px 20px rgba(99, 102, 241, 0.4);
    }
    .button-container {
      text-align: center;
      margin-top: 2rem;
    }
    code {
      background: rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.6);
      padding: 0.2rem 0.4rem;
      border-radius: 3px;
      font-family: 'Courier New', monospace;
      font-size: 0.875rem;
      color: #a78bfa;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <%- include('../partials/header', { user: user }) %>

  <div class="notes-container">
    <div class="notes-header">
      <h1>Patch Notes - v8.0.6</h1>
      <div class="notes-meta">
        <span>January 3, 2025</span>
        <span>•</span>
        <span>Build 8.0.6 "Session Wrap & Documentation"</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Overview -->
    <div class="section">
      <h2>Overview</h2>
      <p>The v8.0.6 "Session Wrap & Documentation" update finalizes the terminal interface overhaul from v8.0.5 with comprehensive documentation updates and session cleanup. This maintenance release ensures all patch notes are properly archived and the development documentation is current.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Documentation Updates -->
    <div class="section">
      <h2>Documentation Updates <span class="badge badge-improvement">Enhanced</span></h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Patch Notes Archive:</strong> Added collapsible Previous Versions section for historical releases</li>
        <li><strong>v8.0.5 Documentation:</strong> Comprehensive terminal overlay implementation details archived</li>
        <li><strong>Version History:</strong> Organized patch notes with v8.0.5 "Terminal Interface Overhaul" and v0.4.0 "Foundation Arc"</li>
        <li><strong>CLAUDE.md Updates:</strong> Development documentation updated with latest session summary</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- What's New Since Last Release -->
    <div class="section">
      <h2>What Changed in v8.0.5</h2>
      <p>The previous release (v8.0.5 "Terminal Interface Overhaul") introduced comprehensive terminal-themed overlays for Character, Inventory, and Profile systems. See full details in the Previous Versions section below.</p>

      <div class="info-box">
        <strong>ℹ️ Maintenance Release:</strong> v8.0.6 focuses on documentation and session cleanup with no gameplay changes.
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Next Steps -->
    <div class="section">
      <h2>Next Steps - v8.0.7 Roadmap Preview</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>System Map Overlays:</strong> Complete terminal overlay implementation in system view</li>
        <li><strong>Equipment System:</strong> Full character equipment loadout functionality</li>
        <li><strong>Ship Fittings:</strong> Complete ship module fitting system with slot management</li>
        <li><strong>Storehouse Network:</strong> Hub-based storage with location switching</li>
        <li><strong>Profile Expansion:</strong> Character list, achievements, and statistics tracking</li>
        <li><strong>Header Integration:</strong> Update header.ejs to use new terminal overlay functions</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- Previous Versions -->
    <div class="section" style="margin-top: 4rem; border-top: 2px solid rgba(99, 102, 241, 0.2); padding-top: 2rem;">
      <h2 style="text-align: center; margin-bottom: 2rem;">Previous Versions</h2>

      <details style="background: rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.6); border: 1px solid rgba(99, 102, 241, 0.3); border-radius: 8px; padding: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 2rem;">
        <summary style="font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 600; color: #8b5cf6; cursor: pointer; user-select: none;">
          v8.0.5 - Terminal Interface Overhaul (January 3, 2025)
        </summary>

        <div style="margin-top: 1.5rem; padding-top: 1.5rem; border-top: 1px solid rgba(99, 102, 241, 0.2);">
          <h3 style="color: #6366f1; margin-bottom: 1rem;">Overview</h3>
          <p>The v8.0.5 "Terminal Interface Overhaul" update introduces comprehensive terminal-themed overlays for Character, Inventory, and Profile systems, matching The Tome's aesthetic with color-coded themes and unified design language.</p>

          <h3 style="color: #6366f1; margin-top: 2rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">Terminal Overlay System</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Character Terminal Overlay:</strong> Blue-themed (#0066ff) terminal interface for character management</li>
            <li><strong>Inventory Terminal Overlay:</strong> Cyan-themed (#00ffff) terminal with split-view layout</li>
            <li><strong>Profile Terminal Overlay:</strong> Purple-themed (#8a4fff) terminal for user account information</li>
            <li><strong>Unified Terminal Aesthetic:</strong> All overlays match The Tome's design language with color-coded themes</li>
            <li><strong>Terminal Prompts:</strong> Authentic command-line style prompts (root@stringborn:~/path/tab$)</li>
            <li><strong>Sidebar Navigation:</strong> Tabbed navigation with active state indicators and item counts</li>
            <li><strong>Blinking Cursor Animations:</strong> Terminal-authentic visual effects throughout</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 style="color: #6366f1; margin-top: 2rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">Character Terminal Features</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Overview Tab:</strong> Character name, species, level, location, and credits display</li>
            <li><strong>Attributes Tab:</strong> Strength, Intelligence, Charisma, Perception, and Willpower stats</li>
            <li><strong>Skills Tab:</strong> Skills system framework (ready for expansion)</li>
            <li><strong>Biography Tab:</strong> Character backstory and lore information</li>
            <li><strong>Terminal Path:</strong> Dynamic path display showing current tab (~/character/overview)</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 style="color: #6366f1; margin-top: 2rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">Inventory Terminal Features</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Three Storage Tabs:</strong> Backpack, Ship Cargo, and Storehouse with separate management</li>
            <li><strong>Split-View Layout:</strong> Left panel shows Equipment/Fittings/Locations, right panel shows items grid</li>
            <li><strong>Item Counts:</strong> Real-time item counts displayed on each tab</li>
            <li><strong>Capacity Display:</strong> Visual capacity indicators for each storage type</li>
            <li><strong>Equipment Panel:</strong> Character loadout visualization (backpack tab)</li>
            <li><strong>Ship Fittings Panel:</strong> Module fittings interface (ship tab)</li>
            <li><strong>Storage Locations Panel:</strong> Hub-based storage facilities (storehouse tab)</li>
            <li><strong>Item Icons:</strong> Visual item type indicators with emoji icons</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 style="color: #6366f1; margin-top: 2rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">Profile Terminal Features</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Account Tab:</strong> Username, email, member since date, and character count</li>
            <li><strong>Characters Tab:</strong> Character list framework (ready for expansion)</li>
            <li><strong>Achievements Tab:</strong> Achievement system framework (ready for expansion)</li>
            <li><strong>Statistics Tab:</strong> Player statistics framework (ready for expansion)</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 style="color: #6366f1; margin-top: 2rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">Technical Improvements</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Unified Terminal System:</strong> Single CSS framework for all terminal-style overlays</li>
            <li><strong>Color-Coded Themes:</strong> Distinct color palettes for each overlay type (blue/cyan/purple/green)</li>
            <li><strong>Early Script Loading:</strong> Critical functions defined before DOM elements for instant onclick access</li>
            <li><strong>Lazy Data Loading:</strong> Overlay data fetched only when first opened</li>
            <li><strong>Glassmorphism Effects:</strong> Subtle backdrop blur (2px) for modern aesthetic</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 style="color: #6366f1; margin-top: 2rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">Bug Fixes</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Import Map Syntax Error:</strong> Fixed JavaScript code incorrectly placed inside JSON importmap block</li>
            <li><strong>Function Not Defined Errors:</strong> Moved navigateWithConfirmation to early script block</li>
            <li><strong>Overlay Menu Exit Button:</strong> Navigation confirmation dialog now properly displays</li>
            <li><strong>Tome Click Handler:</strong> Fixed window.openTomeOverlay availability for onclick handlers</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details style="background: rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.6); border: 1px solid rgba(99, 102, 241, 0.3); border-radius: 8px; padding: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 2rem;">
        <summary style="font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 600; color: #8b5cf6; cursor: pointer; user-select: none;">
          v0.4.0 - Foundation Arc (October 26, 2025)
        </summary>

        <div style="margin-top: 1.5rem; padding-top: 1.5rem; border-top: 1px solid rgba(99, 102, 241, 0.2);">
          <h3 style="color: #6366f1; margin-bottom: 1rem;">Overview</h3>
          <p>The v0.4 "Foundation Arc" update establishes the core systems for the Stringborn Universe. This is our first major public-facing release, bringing together months of infrastructure development into a cohesive, playable experience.</p>

          <h3 style="color: #6366f1; margin-top: 2rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">Galactic Map System</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Live Territory Navigator:</strong> Real-time visualization of faction-controlled zones</li>
            <li><strong>Player Position Streaming:</strong> See other players moving across the galaxy via websockets</li>
            <li><strong>Scatter Repulsion Algorithm:</strong> Natural character positioning preventing overlap</li>
            <li><strong>Quick Start Teleport:</strong> Admin/tester feature for rapid galaxy exploration</li>
            <li><strong>Map Persistence:</strong> Character positions and map state survive server restarts</li>
            <li><strong>Optimized Rendering:</strong> Efficient canvas rendering supporting hundreds of entities</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 style="color: #6366f1; margin-top: 2rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">Character Management</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Character Creation Flow:</strong> Multi-step process with species, faction, and name selection</li>
            <li><strong>Talent Tree System:</strong> Canvas-based skill progression interface (visual demo available)</li>
            <li><strong>Equipment Loadouts:</strong> Equip items, weapons, and gear to characters</li>
            <li><strong>Character Detail View:</strong> Comprehensive stats, inventory, and progression tracking</li>
            <li><strong>Multi-Character Support:</strong> Create and manage multiple characters per account</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 style="color: #6366f1; margin-top: 2rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">Asset Workshop</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Integrated Pixel Editor:</strong> Built-in canvas tool for sprite creation</li>
            <li><strong>Asset Submission Pipeline:</strong> Upload and submit custom content to the community</li>
            <li><strong>Asset Type System:</strong> Support for items, characters, environments, and more</li>
            <li><strong>Community Asset Gallery:</strong> Browse all player-created content</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 style="color: #6366f1; margin-top: 2rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">Voting & Governance</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Democratic Asset Approval:</strong> Community voting determines what enters the universe</li>
            <li><strong>Asset Review Interface:</strong> Detailed view of submissions with voting controls</li>
            <li><strong>Approval Threshold System:</strong> Assets require community consensus to be approved</li>
            <li><strong>Transparent Governance:</strong> All votes and decisions are visible to players</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 style="color: #6366f1; margin-top: 2rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">Real-Time Synchronization</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Socket.io Integration:</strong> Robust websocket infrastructure for live updates</li>
            <li><strong>Connection Resilience:</strong> Automatic reconnection with exponential backoff</li>
            <li><strong>Event Broadcasting:</strong> Efficient server-to-client state synchronization</li>
            <li><strong>Room-Based Channels:</strong> Scoped socket communication for different game areas</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 style="color: #6366f1; margin-top: 2rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">Admin & Developer Tools</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Tester Toolbar:</strong> In-game terminal with realtime socket monitoring</li>
            <li><strong>Telemetry Console:</strong> User behavior analytics and engagement metrics</li>
            <li><strong>Content Moderation Queue:</strong> Review and approve player submissions</li>
            <li><strong>Simulation Controls:</strong> Runtime parameter tuning for game state</li>
            <li><strong>Asset Generator:</strong> Procedural entity creation and batch configuration</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </details>
    </div>

    <!-- Footer -->
    <div class="section" style="text-align: center; border-top: 2px solid rgba(99, 102, 241, 0.3); padding-top: 2rem; margin-top: 3rem;">
      <p style="font-size: 1.25rem; color: #6366f1; font-weight: 600;">Thank you for playing Stringborn Universe!</p>
      <p style="font-style: italic; color: #94a3b8; margin-top: 1rem;">This is just the beginning of our journey together.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="button-container">
      <a href="/menu" class="back-button">← Back to Navigation Hub</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <%- include('../partials/footer') %>
</body>
</html>
